    {
      "id": 1566,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "human",
      "content": "FINDING (Synapse defect, not blocking): `delegate_task` with `task_file: true` overwrites the existing `.synapse/tasks/<id>.md` file with the short message content instead of preserving a separately-authored spec. I authored 100+ lines of spec at the file path, then `delegate_task(task_file=true, content=<short ref>)` clobbered it. The intuitive UX would be: if the file exists, send the short ref pointing at it; if not, write `content` to the file. Worth a small fix in the MCP tool. Restored the spec manually for task 116. Driving on.",
